---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Tagline from '../../components/Tagline.astro';
import ServiceIcon from '../../components/ServiceIcon.astro';
---

<Layout title="Rescue & Refactor - Wellmade" description="Stuck? We unstick things. Product broken. Team gone. Technical debt strangling every new feature. We've seen it. We fix it.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section-primary has-blobs py-20 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <ServiceIcon name="rescue" class="w-14 h-14 text-accent mb-6" />
      <p class="text-accent font-medium mb-4">Services</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold mb-8">Rescue & Refactor</h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-white/80">
        Stuck? We unstick things.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-white/90 mt-4">
        Product broken. Team gone. Technical debt strangling every new feature. We've seen it. We fix it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why It Matters -->
  <section class="section-light py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-title mb-8">Why it matters.</h2>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-body leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Sometimes the best path forward isn't a new build. It's saving what you have.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-body leading-relaxed mb-6">
        You've invested time, money, users. Walking away isn't always the answer. But neither is pretending everything is fine while the codebase rots.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-title font-medium">
        We help you figure out what's worth saving - and actually save it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What It Looks Like -->
  <section class="section-alt py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-title mb-12">What it looks like.</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">Assessment.</h3>
          <p class="text-body">We dig in. Codebase, infrastructure, architecture, processes. We find out what's broken, what's fragile, and what's actually fine.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">Honest diagnosis.</h3>
          <p class="text-body">Sometimes it's fixable. Sometimes it's "burn it down and start over." We'll tell you which, and why.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">Stabilization.</h3>
          <p class="text-body">Stop the bleeding. Fix the critical bugs. Shore up security. Get things running reliably again.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">Refactoring.</h3>
          <p class="text-body">Untangle the mess. Pay down technical debt. Make the codebase something a team can actually work with.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">Knowledge recovery.</h3>
          <p class="text-body">The original team left? We document what we find. We rebuild the tribal knowledge that walked out the door.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">Handover or continue.</h3>
          <p class="text-body">We can hand it back to your team, help you hire, or stick around to keep building.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What You Get -->
  <section class="section-light py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-title mb-8">What you get.</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-4 text-lg text-body">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-primary mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>Clear assessment of what you have and what it'll take to fix</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-primary mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>A stabilized, running product</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-primary mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>Cleaner codebase with less debt</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-primary mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>Documentation that didn't exist before</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-primary mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>A path forward - rebuild, refactor, or retire</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who It's For -->
  <section class="section-primary py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Who it's for.</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-white/80">
            <li>Companies whose dev team left and took all the knowledge</li>
            <li>Products drowning in technical debt</li>
            <li>Startups that built fast and now need to build right</li>
            <li>Anyone who's been told "it needs a complete rewrite" and wants a second opinion</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Who it's not for.</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-white/80">
            <li>"Just make it work, don't ask questions" clients</li>
            <li>Projects where the business case no longer exists</li>
            <li>Quick fixes with no plan for sustainability</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-white/90 mt-6 font-medium">We're not here to duct-tape. If you want a band-aid, we'll tell you it's a band-aid.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Honest Truth -->
  <section class="section-light py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-title mb-8">The honest truth.</h2>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-body leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Sometimes the answer is: don't rescue it. Start fresh.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-title font-medium">
        We'll tell you if that's the case. We'd rather lose an engagement than waste your money on a lost cause.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How We Work Together -->
  <section class="section-alt py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-title mb-8">How we work together.</h2>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-body leading-relaxed mb-6">
        We work in days. Flexible, transparent, no surprises.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-body leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Rescue engagements typically start with a short assessment phase - enough to understand what we're dealing with before committing to a bigger engagement.
      </p>
      <a href="/working-with-us" class="inline-flex items-center text-primary font-semibold hover:text-primary/70 transition-colors group">
        See how we work
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section-light py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-title mb-6">Let's take a look.</h2>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-block bg-primary text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-full font-semibold text-lg hover:bg-primary/90 transition-colors">
        Get in touch
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Tagline />
</Layout>
